Client provides industry leading cloud services and applications for station owners to manage their charging infrastructure, drivers to keep their EVs charged, and for us to efficiently operate the worldwide network of charging stations.
 Maintaining security is critical to building a reliable fueling network for the future of transportation. An engineer in this role will oversee the cloud and client security of our software and will be the go-to person for all things security at different levels of Client software stack.
 You will make things more secure by protecting system boundaries, keeping Client Cloud hardened against attacks and securing sensitive data. 
Responsibilities : 
Define the security architecture for Client cloud & mobile applications. Working with information security and product development teams, develop a roadmap for security initiatives to make the Client network more secure. 
Plan and carry out specific security measures to monitor and protect sensitive data and systems from infiltration and cyber-attacks. Conduct regular audits of our software and perform penetration testing across our software stack. 
Influence Client Software Development and Release processes to avoid information leaks. Spread general awareness and push for best practices to make Client software more secure. 
Stay up to date with latest developments related to software security. 
What You Will Bring to Client 
Strong passion and competency in cloud infrastructure, web & mobile application security & data privacy. 
Previous experience working in a fast-paced, fast-growing, and results-driven environment that demands consistent and enduring excellence. 
Ability to identify issues and develop and implement solutions to meet department and company goals. oStrong organizational skills and the ability to prioritize and manage multiple projects simultaneously with complex and demanding deadlines. 
Ability to work with ambiguity and create quick PoCs 
Requirements : 
8+ years of experience working on software development and distributed systems, with at least 4+ years of hands-on experience focused on securing cloud infrastructure, web and mobile applications. 
Fundamental understanding of security vulnerabilities, attack vectors and tools for mitigation (including DDoS/Bot protection, firewalls, VPNs, authentication & authorization systems, encryption, key management, access management etc.) 
Self-starter, strong drive, bias-to-action, commitment and work ethic; willingness to take on big challenges and own the results from brainstorm to execution. 
Excellent written and verbal communication skills -Able to influence others effectively. 
Preferred 
Experience developing distributed systems and security using AWS. 
Experience with Hashicorp Vault or other secret management solutions. 
Experience improving code security such as static analysis. 
